      "text": [
        " : \"لِلْمُسْرِفِ ثَلاَثُ عَلاَمَاتٍ يَأْكُلُ مَا لَيْسَ لَهُ وَ يَشْتَرِي مَا لَيْسَ لَهُ وَ يَلْبَسُ مَا لَيْسَ لَهُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3624 - Al-Asbagh ibn Nubata narrated from Commander of the Faithful (as) that he said:\n\"The extravagant person has three signs: he eats what does not belong to him, buys what does not belong to him, and wears what does not belong to him.\""
        ]
